WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:10.749
♪ I wake up

00:10.793 --> 00:16.668
♪ With my heart wide open,
oh, yeah ♪

00:16.712 --> 00:20.063
♪ Under the golden sun

00:20.107 --> 00:26.156
♪ Lights so soft
like a sanctuary ♪

00:26.200 --> 00:30.247
♪ But something else
is coming on ♪

00:30.291 --> 00:37.907
♪ Ooh-oh, something dark
has rolled in ♪

00:37.950 --> 00:44.087
♪ Storm has come

00:44.131 --> 00:49.875
♪ Still I hope

00:49.919 --> 00:58.362
♪ Still I won't have no fear

00:58.406 --> 01:03.802
♪ Lay down my burden

01:03.846 --> 01:09.460
♪ Look to the horizon, yeah

01:09.504 --> 01:17.338
♪ And wait for the sun

01:17.381 --> 01:18.730
[ Knock on door ]

01:19.818 --> 01:21.037
Hey.

01:21.081 --> 01:23.300
So it's...
It's Thanksgiving.

01:23.344 --> 01:25.085
[ Sighs ] Yeah, I know.

01:26.782 --> 01:28.914
I'm coming.
Really?

01:28.958 --> 01:30.699
My other options
are staying here

01:30.742 --> 01:34.137
and eating
cold white rice or...

01:34.181 --> 01:36.183
going to my parents'
and getting another lecture

01:36.226 --> 01:38.794
about how much I should
or shouldn't be lifting, so...

01:38.837 --> 01:40.796
yes.

01:40.839 --> 01:42.493
You don't think
it's too soon?

01:42.537 --> 01:44.147
Will you get out of here
so I can change?

01:44.191 --> 01:46.323
Love you. Mean it.

01:46.367 --> 01:48.934
Should I start the car
or you...

01:48.978 --> 01:50.371
Get out. Get out. Get out.You need time.
I'll give you time.

01:50.414 --> 01:52.068
Get...

01:54.026 --> 01:55.115
Okay.

02:05.864 --> 02:07.301
Andy: Hey.

02:07.344 --> 02:09.520
Just dropped a patient off
at Grey Sloan.

02:09.564 --> 02:11.348
Thought I'd check in.

02:11.392 --> 02:12.349
What time's dinner?

02:14.003 --> 02:15.613
Thanksgiving?

02:15.657 --> 02:18.268
[ Sighs ]

02:18.312 --> 02:21.837
It's gonna get better, Jack.
Just takes some time.

02:22.881 --> 02:26.755
[ Gasps ]
Pruitt Arike Miller!

02:26.798 --> 02:29.366
Oh, I've missed you,
mamita!

02:29.410 --> 02:31.281
[ Smooches ]

02:31.325 --> 02:32.717
How's it going
with her?

02:32.761 --> 02:35.024
Surprisingly well, but,
you know, the Millers...

02:35.067 --> 02:36.504
[chuckles]
they're not happy.

02:36.547 --> 02:38.897
I mean, isn't that
what Dean wanted, though?

02:38.941 --> 02:40.290
For you and Miranda
to raise her?

02:40.334 --> 02:42.814
Yes, but you try telling that
to grieving parents

02:42.858 --> 02:44.773
who want
their grandchild, hmm?

02:46.035 --> 02:47.950
Daddy.

02:47.993 --> 02:49.299
♪♪

02:49.343 --> 02:50.561
Yeah.

02:50.605 --> 02:52.128
♪♪

02:52.172 --> 02:54.957
Yeah.
Yeah, that's Daddy.

02:55.000 --> 02:58.439
♪♪

02:58.482 --> 03:00.005
That's your daddy.

03:00.049 --> 03:02.138
♪♪

03:02.182 --> 03:03.226
[ Andy sighs ]

03:03.270 --> 03:05.315
Where's Daddy?

03:05.359 --> 03:09.841
♪♪

03:09.885 --> 03:12.235
Uh, your...

03:12.279 --> 03:16.413
your daddy
is with my daddy.

03:16.457 --> 03:18.676
And -- And they both
love you very much.

03:19.808 --> 03:20.765
[ Smooches ]

03:20.809 --> 03:26.858
♪♪

03:26.902 --> 03:29.252
I'm just saying, the only reason
my dad insists on coming

03:29.296 --> 03:31.341
is because he's sitting on
a lie so big

03:31.385 --> 03:33.735
that he can't bear to be alone
with my mother anymore.

03:33.778 --> 03:35.737
So I'm just supposed
to hand her

03:35.780 --> 03:37.260
a slice
of pumpkin pie

03:37.304 --> 03:39.219
and nottell her that
her marriage is a sham?

03:39.262 --> 03:41.873
Yes, Trav, that's exactly what
you're supposed to do.[ Door opens ]

03:41.917 --> 03:43.614
Sullivan: Hughes?Maya: How are you?

03:43.658 --> 03:44.963
Okay, before
you say anything

03:45.007 --> 03:46.269
or try to blame me
for this,

03:46.313 --> 03:49.751
I tried, but she insisted
on coming and helping.

03:49.794 --> 03:51.274
Did the department
clear you?

03:51.318 --> 03:53.755
I didn't know I needed clearance
for peeling potatoes.

03:54.799 --> 03:56.279
This is
your work environment.

03:56.323 --> 03:57.715
There will be alarms
that could put

03:57.759 --> 03:59.500
undue stress
on your heart.

03:59.543 --> 04:00.849
Thank you, Lieutenant.

04:00.892 --> 04:01.806
I appreciate
the second opinion,

04:01.850 --> 04:02.938
but my heart is fine.

04:02.981 --> 04:04.069
And who was
the first opinion?

04:06.028 --> 04:07.334
Guys, I just need
one thing to feel

04:07.377 --> 04:09.249
just a little bit
normal today,

04:09.292 --> 04:11.207
or is that something that's
gonna make my heart explode?

04:11.251 --> 04:13.470
[ Beeping ]

04:13.514 --> 04:14.906
Vic:
It's fine. It's fine.

04:14.950 --> 04:16.168
I just got a little excited
about the Yukon golds.

04:16.212 --> 04:17.518
I'm fine.

04:18.432 --> 04:19.476
Are you serious?

04:19.520 --> 04:20.912
Okay.

04:22.436 --> 04:24.612
Are you happy?

04:26.004 --> 04:27.179
[ Door opens ]

04:35.231 --> 04:37.494
[ Beeping ]

04:37.538 --> 04:38.887
[ Beeping stops ]

04:38.930 --> 04:40.671
Hughes...

04:40.715 --> 04:42.020
you alright?

04:42.064 --> 04:43.413
Yeah, I'm as okay
as someone can be

04:43.457 --> 04:47.156
after a casual electrocution
and a heart attack.

04:47.199 --> 04:49.550
[ Chuckles ]

04:49.593 --> 04:51.073
It's just an alarm for me
to take a pill.

04:51.116 --> 04:52.770
Um...

04:54.468 --> 04:56.165
How are you...doing?

04:56.208 --> 04:58.341
Gibson...

04:58.385 --> 05:00.735
I'm s-- you gotta
do something.

05:00.778 --> 05:03.041
You can't just sit here
in all this pain.

05:03.085 --> 05:04.434
Otherwise the pain is --

05:06.088 --> 05:07.263
You gotta do something.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.265
I don't want to.Yeah, I know. I know.

05:09.309 --> 05:10.179
But get up anyway,

05:10.222 --> 05:12.834
and why don't
you just go...

05:12.877 --> 05:15.576
I don't --
Go help Travis cook.

05:15.619 --> 05:17.055
I'm serious.[ Pen rattles ]

05:23.584 --> 05:26.369
So I just got word
that the investigation

05:26.413 --> 05:28.937
into my insubordination
is finally happening.

05:28.980 --> 05:30.808
Well, I guess McCallister's
cleaning out his inbox

05:30.852 --> 05:32.157
after the pipeline
explosion.

05:32.201 --> 05:33.594
Is he being blamed
for that?

05:33.637 --> 05:35.552
Not yet.[ Door opens ]

05:35.596 --> 05:37.554
Hey.

05:37.598 --> 05:39.034
It's Thanksgiving.

05:39.077 --> 05:40.601
Sullivan:
Mm-hmm.

05:40.644 --> 05:41.993
So I'm gonna cook.

05:43.255 --> 05:45.257
Well, I'm kinda
already doing that.

05:45.301 --> 05:47.303
Yeah, but now -- now --
now I'm gonna do it.

05:47.347 --> 05:49.261
You know, I-I need this.
It'll be good for me.

05:49.305 --> 05:50.828
Sure, um...
but, I mean,

05:50.872 --> 05:53.440
you know we invited
all of our families,Mm-hmm. Yep.

05:53.483 --> 05:54.615
so there's
a lot of cooking.

05:54.658 --> 05:56.225
Yep, I know.

05:57.574 --> 05:58.923
It's fine.

05:58.967 --> 06:00.490
Okay.

06:01.578 --> 06:02.753
Okay.

06:02.797 --> 06:03.928
Okay.

06:05.103 --> 06:06.757
Are you really gonna let him
just do it all?

06:06.801 --> 06:07.758
[ Faucet runs ]

06:07.802 --> 06:09.238
Well, he's
a pretty good cook,

06:09.281 --> 06:11.632
and I think he needs it
more than I do.
Okay.

06:11.675 --> 06:13.808
Thanks, Gibson.Jack: Yep.

06:14.852 --> 06:16.506
[ Door opens, closes ]

06:18.334 --> 06:20.336
Gibson...

06:20.380 --> 06:21.685
you alright?

06:23.513 --> 06:25.036
Yeah, I'm, uh, cooking.

06:27.299 --> 06:28.518
Right.

06:32.217 --> 06:36.396
[ Sighs ] And this is where
your dad would sit.

06:36.439 --> 06:38.267
Where's Daddy?

06:38.310 --> 06:45.100
♪♪

06:45.143 --> 06:46.406
What's she doing here?

06:46.449 --> 06:49.365
Um...[ Chuckles ]

06:49.409 --> 06:50.540
Thanksgiving.

06:51.889 --> 06:53.848
Yeah, yeah. Sure, yeah.
Of course.

06:53.891 --> 06:56.459
Hey, look who it is!
It's Auntie Vic.

06:56.503 --> 06:58.679
[ Beeping ]

06:58.722 --> 06:59.941
What is that,
a heart-rate tracker?

06:59.984 --> 07:02.117
Um...

07:02.160 --> 07:04.119
You know what? I think Travis
needs help upstairs.

07:04.162 --> 07:06.208
Hughes, you should sit --

07:06.251 --> 07:09.341
[ Alarm beeps ]Dispatch: Engine 19 requested
to 6547 Seaway Place.

07:09.385 --> 07:11.169
[ Groans ]

07:11.213 --> 07:12.257
That's Ingrid's shop.

07:12.301 --> 07:13.737
Again?

07:13.781 --> 07:17.132
Okay, you are gonna
stay here with...

07:17.175 --> 07:18.350
Auntie Maya!

07:18.394 --> 07:19.482
[ Laughs ]

07:19.526 --> 07:21.528
Oh, yeah. You're fine.
You're fine.

07:21.571 --> 07:23.181
Just, uh, you know,
just...

07:23.225 --> 07:24.182
keep her
entertained.

07:24.226 --> 07:25.880
Okay, but why is it
the woman

07:25.923 --> 07:28.230
gets left with the baby
like it's the 1950s, huh?

07:28.273 --> 07:29.623
Can you guys
watch her?

07:29.666 --> 07:32.713
I've got my own
babysitting gig today.

07:32.756 --> 07:37.326
♪♪

07:37.369 --> 07:38.370
Hi.

07:43.027 --> 07:44.376
Why did you send me
to get enough food

07:44.420 --> 07:45.943
for an entire
Thanksgiving dinner

07:45.987 --> 07:48.555
when you already had
everything here?

07:48.598 --> 07:51.514
Because she's captain
and you're a grunt.

07:51.558 --> 07:52.907
She's actingcaptain.

07:52.950 --> 07:55.039
Either way,
show some respect.

07:56.301 --> 08:00.523
We're making extra for
Aquino's and Morse's families.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.046
Firefighters take care
of their own.

08:02.090 --> 08:03.308
Any word on Aquino?

08:03.352 --> 08:06.268
He's out of critical care,
which is good.

08:06.311 --> 08:09.140
He still has a long
road ahead, you know?

08:09.184 --> 08:10.620
So...

08:10.664 --> 08:12.013
where do you want
turkey number two?

08:12.056 --> 08:14.102
Oh, leave it on the counter.
Turkey number one...

08:14.145 --> 08:17.018
is almost ready
to come out.

08:17.061 --> 08:18.541
Wait.
Did I baste already?

08:18.585 --> 08:20.282
Yes, like 30 seconds ago.

08:20.325 --> 08:21.718
God, I'm losing my mind.

08:23.328 --> 08:24.591
[ Sighs ] Okay.

08:24.634 --> 08:26.462
[ Clears throat ]

08:26.506 --> 08:28.943
Did you see
Miller's little girl at 19?

08:28.986 --> 08:30.074
Oh, my God.

08:30.118 --> 08:31.728
She looks
so freakin' cute

08:31.772 --> 08:32.816
in her
Thanksgiving dress.

08:32.860 --> 08:34.775
I wanted to eat
her little arm.

08:34.818 --> 08:35.906
[ Laughs ]

08:37.604 --> 08:39.257
Why the face?

08:39.301 --> 08:41.477
I just...

08:41.521 --> 08:42.870
You know, Vic is going in,

08:42.913 --> 08:45.394
and I don't know
if she's ready to see Pru.

08:45.437 --> 08:47.309
Why? Vic loves Pru.

08:47.352 --> 08:50.704
Yeah, but she's kind of
a walking, talking reminder

08:50.747 --> 08:53.054
that Miller's gone.

08:53.097 --> 08:55.404
And I think she's scared
Pru's mom's gonna come back

08:55.447 --> 08:57.145
and take her to Hong Kong
or something.

08:57.188 --> 08:59.190
J.J.?

08:59.234 --> 09:01.062
You think -- you think
she'll take her back?

09:01.105 --> 09:02.193
I don't know
any of these people.

09:02.237 --> 09:03.717
I'm just saying
what Vic told me.

09:03.760 --> 09:05.066
No, J.J. gave up her right
to be a mom

09:05.109 --> 09:07.155
when she left her daughter
with her father.

09:07.198 --> 09:08.286
I'm...

09:09.940 --> 09:12.552
I got to...
get the groceries.

09:14.379 --> 09:16.251
[ Dissonant notes play ]

09:17.252 --> 09:19.776
Okay. Okay.

09:19.820 --> 09:21.386
So what --
what should we do?

09:21.430 --> 09:27.262
♪♪

09:27.305 --> 09:29.264
[ Whines ]

09:29.307 --> 09:30.265
What? Potty?

09:30.308 --> 09:31.962
I need potty.

09:32.006 --> 09:33.442
Potty? Okay.

09:33.485 --> 09:35.662
Let's go to the bath--
Let's go to the bathroom. Yep.

09:35.705 --> 09:37.402
[ Splattering ][ Gasps ]

09:37.446 --> 09:38.708
Oh, God.

09:38.752 --> 09:41.668
Oh, my God.

09:41.711 --> 09:42.669
[ Laughs ]

09:42.712 --> 09:44.845
Uh...oh...

09:44.888 --> 09:46.847
Help. She's leaking.[ Laughs ]

09:46.890 --> 09:48.022
Give her to me.

09:48.065 --> 09:49.632
Hello, bella.

09:49.676 --> 09:52.374
Oh.Should we get changed?

09:52.417 --> 09:53.549
Oh, God.
It smells so bad.

09:53.593 --> 09:55.595
[ Laughs ]
That's right.

09:55.638 --> 09:58.293
Everybody's poo-poo stinks.

09:58.336 --> 10:00.295
Even Maya's.

10:00.338 --> 10:01.688
♪♪

10:01.731 --> 10:03.428
How are you
so good at this?

10:03.472 --> 10:04.647
You've never babysat?

10:04.691 --> 10:06.431
Oh, thank you.Uh...

10:06.475 --> 10:08.085
Or had friends with kids?

10:09.304 --> 10:10.522
No.

10:10.566 --> 10:12.089
[ Plastic crinkles ]

10:12.133 --> 10:13.656
Nothing?

10:14.788 --> 10:16.920
No.
Yeah, uh-huh.

10:16.964 --> 10:18.618
"Uh-huh" what?

10:18.661 --> 10:19.967
It's nothing.

10:20.010 --> 10:23.710
It just explains a lot
about your personality.

10:23.753 --> 10:26.582
Once you spend a little time
with kids,

10:26.626 --> 10:30.281
you realize that plans and rules
and rigid diets

10:30.325 --> 10:32.588
don't really make sense
when you're always

10:32.632 --> 10:35.460
two minutes away from
an exploding diaper!

10:35.504 --> 10:36.679
[ Giggles ]

10:36.723 --> 10:38.986
[ Laughs ]

10:39.029 --> 10:41.075
And you're all set.

10:41.118 --> 10:43.773
Oh. We might need to
change the socks, too.

10:45.209 --> 10:46.863
Let's see
what color we have...

10:46.907 --> 10:49.257
Pink!
[ Gasps ]
Look at that!

10:49.300 --> 10:51.172
[ Laughs ]

10:51.215 --> 10:52.477
♪♪

10:52.521 --> 10:54.610
Thank you so much for
coming out on a holiday.

10:54.654 --> 10:55.785
I-I'm so embarrassed.

10:55.829 --> 10:57.613
I was sure
I smelled something.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.746
Ingrid, there's no sign
of gas, smoke,

10:59.789 --> 11:02.183
or anything that makes your shop
in any way vulnerable.

11:02.226 --> 11:04.359
Are you positive?
I-I was sure I smelled gas.

11:04.402 --> 11:06.883
Like, so much so that
i-it made me a little dizzy.

11:06.927 --> 11:08.798
These things
are scary accurate, alright?

11:08.842 --> 11:10.191
More sensitive
than drug dogs

11:10.234 --> 11:11.714
or those little, uh --
those little pigs

11:11.758 --> 11:13.020
that look for, um --Truffle pigs.

11:13.063 --> 11:14.412
Yes. Truffle pigs.

11:14.456 --> 11:16.458
Uh, could it be a stroke?
Should I see a doctor?

11:16.501 --> 11:18.634
I mean, don't you smell things
before a stroke?

11:18.678 --> 11:21.158
I-I know I sound paranoid,
but I smelled --

11:21.202 --> 11:22.159
I didn't imagine it.

11:22.203 --> 11:24.118
Okay, look, Ingrid,
the --

11:24.161 --> 11:25.815
the holidays can be tough
when you're grieving,

11:25.859 --> 11:27.599
e-especially after the loss
of a spouse.

11:29.340 --> 11:30.864
You know,
w-we're having Thanksgiving

11:30.907 --> 11:32.126
at the station
this afternoon.

11:32.169 --> 11:33.780
Why don't you drop by,
grab a slice of pie,

11:33.823 --> 11:35.912
and, you know,
be around people?

11:35.956 --> 11:38.741
That's so sweet. I --

11:38.785 --> 11:40.438
Yes, I-I would love to.

11:40.482 --> 11:42.440
Great, okay.
Then we'll see you in a bit.

11:42.484 --> 11:43.746
Okay.Alright. Alright.

11:45.748 --> 11:46.749
She's lonely.

11:46.793 --> 11:48.098
You're asking for it.No, I'm not...

11:49.578 --> 11:51.362
[ Cellphone dings ]

11:51.406 --> 11:53.930
Dad, could you at least
silence your phone?

11:53.974 --> 11:55.715
Then what's the point
of notifications, Travis?

11:55.758 --> 11:57.281
Why do you need
notifications

11:57.325 --> 11:59.414
when you're with your family
on Thanksgiving?

11:59.457 --> 12:01.242
It's the holidays.

12:01.285 --> 12:03.810
I would never ask you not to see
Emmett on the holidays.

12:03.853 --> 12:05.246
Except you would.
And you did.

12:05.289 --> 12:06.813
Because when
I first started dating Michael,

12:06.856 --> 12:08.205
you wouldn't let me invite him
to Christmas dinner.

12:08.249 --> 12:09.598
[ Table thumps ]

12:10.817 --> 12:12.775
Wait a minute.
You --

12:15.038 --> 12:17.214
You're not trying to meet up
with Kyle today, are you?

12:17.258 --> 12:19.173
What I do with my personal life
is none of your business.

12:19.216 --> 12:21.653
Except it is when
it concerns my mother.

12:21.697 --> 12:23.699
Your mother is my wife.

12:23.743 --> 12:25.745
Don't worry about our marriage.
Your mom and I are happy.

12:27.181 --> 12:29.226
I know it's impossible
for you to believe

12:29.270 --> 12:31.228
that anyone could be happy
who doesn't live their life

12:31.272 --> 12:33.709
according to your standards,
but we are.

12:33.753 --> 12:35.755
Well, you're asking me to lie,
and I can't live with that.

12:38.018 --> 12:41.021
Then tell your mother.
Go ahead.

12:41.064 --> 12:42.979
You're not going to,
are you, Travis?

12:43.023 --> 12:44.807
'Cause then you won't have
a reason to write me off

12:44.851 --> 12:47.288
like you do anybody else
who doesn't play by your rules.

12:51.509 --> 12:53.685
Travis...

12:53.729 --> 12:55.035
I love you
and I love your mother.

12:55.078 --> 12:57.037
No, Dad,
you don't love us,

12:57.080 --> 12:58.865
because if you did,
you wouldn't lie to us.

12:58.908 --> 13:01.345
Travis, you've never lied
to anyone to protect them?

13:01.389 --> 13:02.825
Dad, protect who?

13:02.869 --> 13:04.914
The only person that you're
protecting is yourself.

13:04.958 --> 13:07.264
You are having an affair.

13:07.308 --> 13:08.918
Gay or straight,
it doesn't matter.

13:08.962 --> 13:10.572
When you met Emmett,
he was engaged to someone else.

13:10.615 --> 13:12.008
That is such --

13:12.879 --> 13:14.576
[ Cellphone dings ]

13:15.795 --> 13:18.536
Um, I have an idea.

13:18.580 --> 13:20.582
Why don't we do that thing,
you know,

13:20.625 --> 13:23.454
where you go around and say
what you're grateful for?

13:25.065 --> 13:27.067
Isn't that a "dinner table"
thing, Paul?

13:27.110 --> 13:29.765
We can occupy ourselves
while we work.

13:29.809 --> 13:31.854
Emmett: I think
that's really cute, right?

13:31.898 --> 13:33.377
I-I-I'll go first.

13:33.421 --> 13:35.902
Uh, okay,
in this, uh, you know,

13:35.945 --> 13:37.294
uncertain world,

13:37.338 --> 13:39.688
I am grateful for my love.

13:41.124 --> 13:42.865
Um...

13:42.909 --> 13:46.826
I am grateful I got out of bed
this morning.

13:48.523 --> 13:50.568
Trav? You want to...?

13:51.656 --> 13:53.658
Yeah, yeah. I'll go.

13:53.702 --> 13:58.054
Uh, I'm grateful for truth.
Yeah, you know?

13:58.098 --> 14:02.015
'Cause life is too short
to live it in a lie.

14:02.058 --> 14:04.408
Yeah, uh, Nari,
why don't you go next?

14:04.452 --> 14:05.888
Oh, me?
Yeah.

14:05.932 --> 14:08.935
Well, I'm grateful
for my son,

14:08.978 --> 14:10.937
and for Emmett,

14:10.980 --> 14:12.286
and for my loving husband,
Paul.

14:12.329 --> 14:13.461
Travis: Aww.

14:13.504 --> 14:15.245
Dad, why don't you go?

14:15.289 --> 14:16.812
Are you grateful
for you loving wife?

14:16.856 --> 14:18.205
For God's sake, Travis --That's a terrible start,
Dad.

14:18.248 --> 14:19.336
Would you stop it?!

14:19.380 --> 14:21.861
You push and you push
and you push

14:21.904 --> 14:23.819
and you don't know
when to quit!

14:23.863 --> 14:24.559
Honey!

14:24.602 --> 14:26.169
I'm gay, alright?

14:26.213 --> 14:27.954
I'm in love with a man!

14:27.997 --> 14:31.261
And my son won't give me
one day of peace!

14:31.305 --> 14:32.872
♪♪

14:32.915 --> 14:34.699
[ Laughs ]

14:34.743 --> 14:39.095
♪♪

14:39.139 --> 14:40.270
Travis: Mom...

14:40.314 --> 14:42.316
Excuse me.

14:42.359 --> 14:46.755
♪♪

14:46.798 --> 14:48.670
[ Laughs ]
I'm sorry.

14:48.713 --> 14:50.324
I'm grateful for
nervous laughter.

14:50.367 --> 14:52.761
Travis.

14:52.804 --> 14:57.157
♪♪

15:00.421 --> 15:02.814
Mom. Mom, wait.Travis, I do not want
to speak to you.

15:02.858 --> 15:04.947
To me?You had to push him.

15:04.991 --> 15:06.166
I didn't, Mom.

15:06.209 --> 15:08.908
I saw you.
The constant harassing.

15:08.951 --> 15:11.432
We would have been fine
if you hadn't said anything.

15:11.475 --> 15:13.347
Wait, did...you know?

15:13.390 --> 15:15.392
Of course not.

15:15.436 --> 15:18.308
I knew something was off.

15:18.352 --> 15:20.658
Our sex life hasn't been
the same for years...Oh, God.

15:20.702 --> 15:22.704
...but we still go to
the farmers' market together

15:22.747 --> 15:24.314
every weekend,

15:24.358 --> 15:27.404
and he helps me do the dishes
every night after dinner.

15:27.448 --> 15:30.755
Our little things.
No marriage is perfect.

15:30.799 --> 15:32.888
Why did you have to
push him?

15:32.932 --> 15:35.717
[ Footsteps departing ]

15:35.760 --> 15:38.459
[ Water boiling,
door opens ]

15:39.721 --> 15:41.027
Oh, my.

15:41.070 --> 15:42.071
Mrs. Montgomery,
I-I-I was gonna --

15:42.115 --> 15:43.377
You're making a mess.
Give me that.

15:43.420 --> 15:45.074
No, I was gonna do it
on my own,

15:45.118 --> 15:46.858
if that's --
I'm just trying to --No, you weren't.

15:46.902 --> 15:48.382
I'm helping.

15:48.425 --> 15:49.861
[ Beeping ]

15:49.905 --> 15:51.385
Stop!

15:51.428 --> 15:53.822
Sorry, it's the --
the watch.

15:55.650 --> 15:56.956
What are you doing,
Nari?

15:56.999 --> 15:58.261
Cooking.

15:58.305 --> 15:59.262
Why?

15:59.306 --> 16:00.960
It soothes me.

16:01.003 --> 16:02.874
People think they know
what's best for you.

16:02.918 --> 16:05.181
Keeping information and then
doling it out as they see fit

16:05.225 --> 16:06.878
to "protect" you.

16:08.576 --> 16:10.273
When it just hurts worse
than the thing they think

16:10.317 --> 16:11.709
they're protecting
you from, right?

16:13.581 --> 16:14.756
Because in addition
to the pain

16:14.799 --> 16:17.280
of the actual thing,
you think,

16:17.324 --> 16:20.022
"Did everyone just think
I couldn't deal with the truth?"

16:20.066 --> 16:21.545
And then
it's too late anyway,

16:21.589 --> 16:24.331
because the truth
just exploded,

16:24.374 --> 16:25.158
like it does.

16:25.201 --> 16:26.811
Exactly.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.944
Though I suppose I now have
all the information,

16:28.988 --> 16:31.120
and it doesn't feel
very good, either.

16:31.164 --> 16:34.558
You know, I used to think
things happened for a reason.

16:34.602 --> 16:37.997
But the truth is,
there's nothing.
There's no meaning.

16:38.040 --> 16:39.520
[ Chuckles ]
You know, you're --

16:39.563 --> 16:41.043
You're in a building or
you're outside of a building.

16:41.087 --> 16:43.089
The building blows up
or it doesn't blow up.

16:43.132 --> 16:44.786
Your best friend's
in love with you

16:44.829 --> 16:46.266
or he isn't
in love with you.

16:46.309 --> 16:48.094
You live and you die,
and...

16:48.137 --> 16:50.618
It's all just random,
meaningless cruelty.

16:50.661 --> 16:52.272
Is that supposed to
make me feel better?

16:52.315 --> 16:55.449
[ Clattering ]

16:55.492 --> 16:57.320
Sorry. I'm sorry.

16:57.712 --> 16:58.974
[ Door opens ]

16:59.018 --> 17:01.194
Hey. Where is she?

17:01.237 --> 17:03.065
In the...?It's okay. It's okay.

17:03.109 --> 17:05.850
She -- She's upstairs
with Bishop and DeLuca.

17:05.894 --> 17:07.809
[ Sighs ] Oh. Sorry.

17:07.852 --> 17:12.248
J-- That call from the lawyers
has me on high alert,

17:12.292 --> 17:15.469
'cause they are her family,
and if they want --

17:15.512 --> 17:17.471
Miranda, you know
better than anyone

17:17.514 --> 17:19.516
that blood does not
a family make.

17:19.560 --> 17:21.388
Weare also her family.

17:21.431 --> 17:23.564
[ Footsteps approaching ]

17:23.607 --> 17:24.869
Oh.

17:24.913 --> 17:25.914
Ben.

17:25.957 --> 17:27.481
Oh, "Ben"?

17:27.524 --> 17:28.656
[ Sighs, chuckles ]

17:28.699 --> 17:31.093
Um, Ingrid, uh,
this is Miranda.

17:31.137 --> 17:32.529
Dr. Miranda Bailey.

17:32.573 --> 17:34.140
And you are?

17:34.183 --> 17:36.533
Ingrid Saunders.
I live in the neighborhood.

17:36.577 --> 17:39.058
I'm gonna go
check on Pru.

17:39.101 --> 17:40.885
Okay.

17:40.929 --> 17:45.542
♪♪

17:45.586 --> 17:47.892
Miranda is...
My wife.

17:49.720 --> 17:51.809
Oh.

17:51.853 --> 17:53.681
Oh, of course.

17:53.724 --> 17:55.204
Yes, you're --
you're married.

17:55.248 --> 17:57.772
Mm-hmm.
Um...

17:57.815 --> 17:59.774
You know what?
I'm gonna -- I'm gonna go.

17:59.817 --> 18:02.124
Uh, keep the pie.
It's the least I can do.Um, I-Ingrid,
Ingrid, Ingrid.

18:02.168 --> 18:04.605
Ingrid, please.
Just -- [sighs] stay.

18:04.648 --> 18:06.476
You don't have to
be alone today.

18:06.520 --> 18:08.130
♪♪

18:08.174 --> 18:09.610
Just, um --

18:09.653 --> 18:13.309
♪♪

18:13.353 --> 18:14.136
[ Sighs ]

18:14.180 --> 18:18.923
♪♪

18:18.967 --> 18:20.142
[ Sighs ]

18:23.624 --> 18:25.843
Miller was clear on
what he wanted.

18:25.887 --> 18:28.194
He wanted Warren
to raise Pru.

18:28.237 --> 18:30.544
J.J. doesn't get to
have a say, not one word.

18:30.587 --> 18:32.937
And I'm sorry, but
neither do Miller's parents.

18:32.981 --> 18:35.940
Miller raised that baby.
He raised her.

18:35.984 --> 18:38.813
He did the work.
He poured the love in.

18:38.856 --> 18:40.858
Her Station 19 family
picked up the slack,

18:40.902 --> 18:42.382
so no one
gets to take her away.

18:42.425 --> 18:43.165
[ Timer dings ]

18:43.209 --> 18:46.299
So, uh...

18:46.342 --> 18:49.302
Did you know that Miller
was in love with Vic?

18:49.345 --> 18:51.347
Please tell me you're not
so insecure in your manhood

18:51.391 --> 18:53.175
that you're jealous
of Dean.

18:53.219 --> 18:54.829
He's gone.

18:56.222 --> 18:58.572
He's -- He's -- He's --

18:58.615 --> 19:00.226
[ Pounds on counter ]
He's dead!

19:00.269 --> 19:01.966
And Vic had a --
had a heart attack.

19:02.010 --> 19:03.185
How are you making this
about you?

19:03.229 --> 19:04.534
Whoa.

19:04.578 --> 19:07.015
How am I...?

19:07.058 --> 19:09.104
[ Scoffs ]

19:09.148 --> 19:11.498
You know,
why is everyone else

19:11.541 --> 19:13.935
allowed to process their
feelings around here but me?

19:13.978 --> 19:15.763
I didn't say I was
losing sleep over it.

19:15.806 --> 19:17.591
I'm just talking to my friend
about something

19:17.634 --> 19:22.291
that...I don't know, kind of
feels like a big deal to me.

19:22.335 --> 19:25.990
Sorry that my worries aren't
as important as yours, Captain.

19:26.034 --> 19:27.035
Damn.

19:27.078 --> 19:29.820
[ Chuckling ]

19:32.083 --> 19:34.216
Hysterical/historical.

19:35.261 --> 19:36.653
What?

19:36.697 --> 19:39.308
I'm hysterical,
which I have been told means

19:39.352 --> 19:41.702
that it's historical.
It's --

19:41.745 --> 19:45.096
I'm -- I'm making
Miller's death

19:45.140 --> 19:48.274
and that poor little girl's
life all about me.

19:48.317 --> 19:51.668
And I'm mad at you
because I'm mad at the world,

19:51.712 --> 19:53.888
because I'm mad
at my own mother.

19:57.239 --> 19:59.937
[ Sighs ]

19:59.981 --> 20:02.201
[ Quietly ] Damn.

20:10.296 --> 20:14.778
I-I didn't know
Miller was in love with Vic,

20:14.822 --> 20:17.085
but once I found out,
it made sense.

20:17.128 --> 20:20.871
But I don't think
she loved him back.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.438
Because if she did,
she would have recognized

20:22.482 --> 20:23.918
that he loved her,
and instead,

20:23.961 --> 20:26.181
she just
chose not to see it.

20:26.225 --> 20:31.795
♪♪

20:34.320 --> 20:35.451
Hey, I've been looking
for you.

20:35.495 --> 20:36.887
I needed a shower.

20:38.628 --> 20:40.761
You are
very understanding

20:40.804 --> 20:43.677
and very forgiving
of my father.

20:43.720 --> 20:45.635
Because I've been
where he is.

20:45.679 --> 20:48.334
Yeah, that man didn't
show up to my wedding,

20:48.377 --> 20:51.250
and he didn't let my mom
come, either.

20:51.293 --> 20:54.296
And I understand that
he was mired in self-loathing.

20:54.340 --> 20:56.298
I get that now.

20:56.342 --> 20:58.387
But does that mean that
all the pain that he caused

20:58.431 --> 21:00.737
my whole life and the pain
that he's causing my mother now,

21:00.781 --> 21:03.174
that it's just --
it's nothing?

21:03.218 --> 21:05.481
It's just
instantly forgiven?

21:05.525 --> 21:07.701
I need you on myside.

21:07.744 --> 21:08.876
And, yeah, that --

21:08.919 --> 21:12.401
It's selfish
and it's irrational.

21:12.445 --> 21:14.055
♪♪

21:14.098 --> 21:16.013
But I'm in pain, too.

21:16.057 --> 21:18.102
I know. I...

21:18.146 --> 21:20.453
It would just be nice
if someone could...

21:20.496 --> 21:22.324
you know, be on my side.

21:22.368 --> 21:24.370
[ Boot zips ]

21:24.413 --> 21:26.633
Trav, there are no
sides here, okay?

21:26.676 --> 21:29.679
No. I'm sorry.
I love you.

21:29.723 --> 21:31.551
But there's work
to be done.

21:31.594 --> 21:34.031
♪♪

21:34.075 --> 21:35.511
[ Door opens ]

21:40.821 --> 21:42.126
Not officially back.

21:42.170 --> 21:44.433
But --
No, I'm not. I just --

21:44.477 --> 21:46.305
I did just find out

21:46.348 --> 21:48.916
that this is where
I'm gonna be benched

21:48.959 --> 21:50.091
for the next
several weeks

21:50.134 --> 21:52.049
while my fragile, fragile
heart heals.

21:52.093 --> 21:53.355
Mm.

21:55.270 --> 21:58.882
Hey, thank you for...
taking over Crisis One.

22:00.101 --> 22:01.972
It means a lot, and I'll be
ready to help again soon.

22:02.016 --> 22:03.409
It's just --

22:03.452 --> 22:05.628
Sullivan's been helping.

22:05.672 --> 22:08.544
And Warren
and Montgomery.

22:08.588 --> 22:11.982
That program will not die
with Dean Miller.

22:12.026 --> 22:13.680
It's his legacy,
and we will all protect it.

22:13.723 --> 22:15.725
[ Beeping ]

22:15.769 --> 22:16.813
That sounds concerning.

22:16.857 --> 22:19.773
Oh, it's not.
It's just my heart.

22:19.816 --> 22:21.775
Your heart
is not concerning?

22:21.818 --> 22:24.255
Metaphor. Cool. Okay.[ Stammers ]

22:24.299 --> 22:25.692
[ Both laugh ]

22:25.735 --> 22:27.215
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

22:27.258 --> 22:28.999
Thanks for the pie.Mm-hmm.

22:29.043 --> 22:31.393
And, you know,
thanks for checking in.

22:31.437 --> 22:33.177
I don't want to keep you
from your family,

22:33.221 --> 22:34.744
so I'll -- I'll take this
upstairs for you.

22:36.311 --> 22:37.573
Nothing you want
to get off your chest?

22:37.617 --> 22:38.966
Um...

22:39.009 --> 22:41.621
You know,
I'm just kinda...

22:41.664 --> 22:43.144
doing my thing.

22:43.187 --> 22:45.755
You know,
my push through it and...

22:45.799 --> 22:47.540
keep it light
and feel the feelings

22:47.583 --> 22:49.803
but don't dwell
on them thing.

22:52.414 --> 22:54.677
The truth is, I want to
crawl into a hole.

23:00.509 --> 23:01.989
And I want to let
that hole swallow me

23:02.032 --> 23:04.295
and hope that
no one finds me.

23:04.339 --> 23:06.428
And why can't you
let yourself do that?

23:06.472 --> 23:09.866
Because everyone expects me
to be me and to make jokes

23:09.910 --> 23:13.435
and make them
feel better and...

23:13.479 --> 23:17.396
laugh through the tears,
like I did when Lucas...

23:17.439 --> 23:19.006
♪♪

23:19.049 --> 23:21.878
Why do you care about
what they expect?

23:21.922 --> 23:23.445
[ Sighs ]
Because if I don't,

23:23.489 --> 23:26.274
it means that this death
hurt more than that one,

23:26.317 --> 23:28.581
and I can't let that be true,
'cause it's...

23:30.670 --> 23:32.236
It's not.

23:32.280 --> 23:33.977
♪♪

23:34.021 --> 23:39.635
We all have
a psychological immune system.

23:39.679 --> 23:42.029
Just like our physiological
immune system

23:42.072 --> 23:44.466
helps our bodies recover
from physical attacks,

23:44.510 --> 23:46.555
our brains are working
to protect us

23:46.599 --> 23:48.339
from psychological ones.

23:48.383 --> 23:50.254
Maybe when
your fiancé died,

23:50.298 --> 23:52.082
that's how your brain
protected you,

23:52.126 --> 23:55.085
and now it's dealing with
the attack a little differently.

23:57.000 --> 23:58.959
Yeah.

24:01.178 --> 24:03.354
Miller was --

24:03.398 --> 24:05.444
He was in love with me,
it turns out.

24:05.487 --> 24:06.923
I know.

24:06.967 --> 24:09.535
Why did everybody know that
but me? What --

24:09.578 --> 24:11.232
Psychological
immune system, maybe?

24:11.275 --> 24:12.973
Yeah.

24:13.016 --> 24:14.409
I can't.

24:14.453 --> 24:16.455
Your love for him
can be as real

24:16.498 --> 24:18.979
as it feels
for you right now --

24:19.022 --> 24:23.853
as real and immense and
significant as it was and is

24:23.897 --> 24:26.116
without you having been
in love with him back.

24:28.075 --> 24:29.772
You're punishing yourself

24:29.816 --> 24:31.948
for not being
in love with him back --

24:31.992 --> 24:34.211
something your brain
knew on some level,

24:34.255 --> 24:35.343
because you're not dumb.

24:37.606 --> 24:41.784
You were just afraid of what
would happen if it were true.

24:44.004 --> 24:45.527
[ Sighs ]

24:45.571 --> 24:47.224
Thank you...

24:47.268 --> 24:49.313
for the...

24:49.357 --> 24:50.924
♪♪

24:50.967 --> 24:53.056
...for the pie.

24:53.100 --> 24:56.016
You guys always feel better
when you talk to me.Yeah.

24:56.059 --> 24:57.800
I do not understand

24:57.844 --> 25:00.455
why you always fight
me on it first.

25:02.501 --> 25:04.459
Enjoy that pie.

25:04.503 --> 25:06.243
Thanks.[ Door opens, closes ]

25:06.287 --> 25:13.990
♪♪

25:14.034 --> 25:17.733
Isn't Thanksgiving supposed
to be one of our busier days?

25:17.777 --> 25:20.649
So, uh, Paul?
[ Chuckles ]

25:22.695 --> 25:24.174
What do you do
for work?

25:24.218 --> 25:25.349
Sullivan: Hey, Warren.

25:25.393 --> 25:26.525
Oh, thank God.

25:26.568 --> 25:28.265
That, uh,
woman you invited?

25:28.309 --> 25:30.180
I just saw her wandering
around the locker room.

25:30.224 --> 25:32.139
Um, you invited her?

25:32.182 --> 25:33.575
Wh-- S-She's a widow.

25:33.619 --> 25:34.794
What -- Okay, where'd you
see her last?

25:34.837 --> 25:36.535
I don't know,
poking around the bunks?

25:36.578 --> 25:37.884
Alright. I'll find her.

25:37.927 --> 25:40.713
Yeah, you find her,
and then later,

25:40.756 --> 25:42.453
we're having
a conversation.

25:42.497 --> 25:44.238
[ Chuckles ]

25:44.281 --> 25:46.632
[ Chuckles ]

25:46.675 --> 25:50.113
How are we doing?
Is that a turkey?

25:50.157 --> 25:53.377
Thought you'd be off
with your boyfriend by now.

25:53.421 --> 25:55.423
I'm not leaving.

25:55.466 --> 25:56.990
I love your mother.

25:57.033 --> 25:58.208
I'm sorry for the way
things came out,

25:58.252 --> 25:59.601
but...

25:59.645 --> 26:02.125
I'm not sorry I said it.

26:02.169 --> 26:05.215
I feel...free.

26:05.259 --> 26:08.305
I have held onto that
for decades.

26:08.349 --> 26:10.046
I never let myself
feel okay.

26:10.090 --> 26:12.614
I never let myself feel.

26:12.658 --> 26:14.573
I'm not you.

26:14.616 --> 26:17.706
I'm not brave like you.

26:17.750 --> 26:20.491
But I'm learning
from your example,

26:20.535 --> 26:21.884
so I'm not leaving.

26:21.928 --> 26:23.712
I want your mom to know
that I'm here.

26:23.756 --> 26:25.888
I want her to know that,
at least.

26:25.932 --> 26:28.369
I'm still here for her...

26:28.412 --> 26:30.284
and I'm still here
for you.

26:30.327 --> 26:35.115
♪♪

26:35.158 --> 26:37.900
I'm gonna, uh...
grab more dishes.

26:37.944 --> 26:44.211
♪♪

26:44.254 --> 26:46.126
He'll come around.

26:46.169 --> 26:48.171
Sorry, w-we haven't met.

26:48.215 --> 26:49.608
Paul. Paul Montgomery.

26:49.651 --> 26:51.958
Paul. Hi, uh,
Dr. Miranda Bailey.

26:52.001 --> 26:53.350
Hi.

26:53.394 --> 26:54.351
Happy Thanksgiving.

26:54.395 --> 26:55.788
Happy Thanksgiving.

26:57.572 --> 26:59.748
[ Sighs ]

26:59.792 --> 27:01.184
[ Door closes ]

27:01.228 --> 27:02.925
I feel so stupid.
[ Laughs ]

27:02.969 --> 27:04.971
You're married.
Of course you are.

27:05.014 --> 27:06.581
I-I'm sorry
if I ever gave you

27:06.625 --> 27:08.365
the wrong impression
about my intentions.

27:08.409 --> 27:11.412
Yeah, that -- that's
like an "I'm sorry you
feel that way" sorry.

27:11.455 --> 27:13.327
[ Sighs ]I don't know how
I got this so wrong.

27:13.370 --> 27:14.110
Ingrid,
I never meant to --

27:14.154 --> 27:15.590
I know!

27:15.634 --> 27:17.374
Please stop saying that.
It's more embarrassing.

27:17.418 --> 27:19.202
You have nothing to be
embarrassed about.

27:19.246 --> 27:22.553
You invited me here like
a stray dog you felt bad for,

27:22.597 --> 27:24.686
and I thought
it was a date.

27:24.730 --> 27:26.688
[ Laughs ]

27:26.732 --> 27:28.821
Just put out a bowl of water
for me.

27:28.864 --> 27:29.822
I'll be fine.

27:29.865 --> 27:31.258
Ingrid.
Ingrid, look at me.

27:31.301 --> 27:32.651
Have you ever
lost anyone?

27:34.740 --> 27:37.525
Actually...Someone you loved?

27:37.568 --> 27:42.661
Someone you'd slept beside
every night for 10 years?

27:42.704 --> 27:46.839
No. Not --
Not someone like that.

27:46.882 --> 27:48.579
Ugh, I didn't used to
be like this!

27:48.623 --> 27:50.320
I used to like being alone,

27:50.364 --> 27:52.279
but...[sobbing]

27:52.322 --> 27:57.980
Scott, he became
a part of me, and now...

27:58.024 --> 27:59.329
and now...

27:59.373 --> 28:00.983
Ingrid. Ingrid.
Ingrid, no, no, no, no!

28:01.027 --> 28:02.245
No, Ingrid, listen to me.

28:02.289 --> 28:04.683
No, no, no, please,
just leave me alone.

28:04.726 --> 28:07.337
♪♪

28:07.381 --> 28:09.339
I want to be alone.

28:09.383 --> 28:11.777
♪♪

28:14.997 --> 28:16.259
Ingrid, please.

28:16.303 --> 28:17.521
I can't. [ Sniffles ]

28:17.565 --> 28:20.742
I can't do this anymore.
[ Sniffles ] I can't.

28:20.786 --> 28:22.265
Ingrid.

28:22.309 --> 28:24.137
No, no, no.
J-J-Just stay -- stay back.

28:24.180 --> 28:26.313
Look, this building
is not that tall, okay?

28:26.356 --> 28:27.836
If you jump, the worst
that's gonna happen is,

28:27.880 --> 28:29.533
you break both your legs
and you're in terrible pain.

28:29.577 --> 28:32.275
Yeah, well, that sounds better
than how I feel right now.

28:32.319 --> 28:34.669
Besides,
then I won't be alone.

28:34.713 --> 28:37.193
I'll -- I'll be
in the hospital and --

28:37.237 --> 28:40.457
and people will check on me
and bring me food.

28:40.501 --> 28:43.547
Do you know what it's like
to cook for yourself

28:43.591 --> 28:46.899
all by yourself every day,
all the time?

28:46.942 --> 28:48.552
The hospital sounds better
than that.

28:48.596 --> 28:50.250
Well, your next meal
won't be alone

28:50.293 --> 28:53.079
if you'd just come downstairs
and e-eat with us.

28:53.122 --> 28:54.863
Yeah, what would your wife
say about that?

28:55.342 --> 28:56.691
Ingrid.

28:56.735 --> 28:59.085
I'm sorry. [ Sniffles ]
What am I even saying?

28:59.128 --> 29:02.088
I-It's not even --
It's not about --

29:02.131 --> 29:05.091
♪♪

29:05.918 --> 29:07.441
No one
would even miss me.

29:07.484 --> 29:08.877
That's not true.

29:08.921 --> 29:13.403
I might break
both my legs, but...

29:13.447 --> 29:15.362
but maybe I'll get lucky

29:15.405 --> 29:17.756
and hit my head
and never wake up.

29:17.799 --> 29:24.588
♪♪

29:26.112 --> 29:27.591
[ Sighs ]

29:27.635 --> 29:31.247
You know, Jack,
I...lost my brother, too.

29:31.291 --> 29:33.075
And it feels like...

29:33.119 --> 29:35.599
like you can't get
air in your lungs,

29:35.643 --> 29:38.951
like...like nothing
will ever be okay again,

29:38.994 --> 29:41.736
like you will never
feel joy again.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.303
So you try to
push it down,

29:43.346 --> 29:45.871
and you try not to feel it,
and the awful irony is that

29:45.914 --> 29:50.658
the further you push it down,
the longer it stays.

29:50.701 --> 29:52.355
So you have to
let it out --

29:52.399 --> 29:55.141
to cry, to laugh,
and -- and cry again --

29:55.184 --> 29:56.795
which is all the same thing,
by the way,

29:56.838 --> 29:58.840
crying and laughing
and -- and screaming

29:58.884 --> 30:00.711
and -- and dancing.

30:00.755 --> 30:02.844
I-It lets it
out of your body,

30:02.888 --> 30:04.063
and you need it
out of your body,

30:04.106 --> 30:08.067
because --
because when it comes out,

30:08.110 --> 30:11.766
it makes room for light
to come back in.

30:12.898 --> 30:16.336
Why do I smell...smoke?!

30:16.379 --> 30:17.424
Oh, my God.

30:17.467 --> 30:20.906
♪♪

30:20.949 --> 30:22.124
It's locked!

30:22.168 --> 30:24.039
It was set to "clean"
instead of "bake."

30:24.083 --> 30:25.606
Maya: Oh, come on,
I can't put it out

30:25.649 --> 30:26.781
if we can't get
in there.

30:26.825 --> 30:28.000
Come on, pull.

30:28.043 --> 30:29.697
♪♪

30:29.740 --> 30:33.266
It feels so spiky and awful
and I just...[Sniffles]

30:33.309 --> 30:35.268
I should be at
the acceptance phase already.

30:35.311 --> 30:37.748
I-It's been over a year.
I don't get it.

30:37.792 --> 30:39.141
I just don't get it.

30:39.185 --> 30:42.014
Who says you should be
at acceptance yet?

30:42.057 --> 30:45.191
A year, it -- it --
it's not that long,

30:45.234 --> 30:47.889
n-not for grief.

30:47.933 --> 30:50.892
That -- That study,
[laughs] uh, the five stages?

30:50.936 --> 30:52.981
It's, um --

30:53.025 --> 30:55.418
It's crap, okay?
I-It's utter nonsense.

30:55.462 --> 30:58.987
It -- It -- It was about
terminally ill patients

30:59.031 --> 31:02.338
coming to terms
with their owndeath.

31:02.382 --> 31:04.863
I mean, a person accepting
the end of their own life

31:04.906 --> 31:06.865
is totally different
than accepting

31:06.908 --> 31:09.693
losing someone you love.

31:09.737 --> 31:12.479
Look, we -- we --
we're, um...

31:12.522 --> 31:16.135
We're all living that
firsthand right now.

31:17.876 --> 31:19.790
You sign up to be
a firefighter,

31:19.834 --> 31:20.879
on some level
you're accepting

31:20.922 --> 31:24.621
that you could
lose your own life.

31:24.665 --> 31:26.928
B-But, um, when it's --

31:26.972 --> 31:28.843
when it's someone else's,
you know,

31:28.887 --> 31:32.673
one of your brothers
or sisters,

31:32.716 --> 31:36.851
I-I don't know how
we'll ever "accept" that.

31:38.548 --> 31:41.334
I-I'm not sure
we ever will.

31:41.377 --> 31:44.119
♪♪

31:44.163 --> 31:45.033
[ Alarm blaring ]

31:45.077 --> 31:46.208
What is happening?!

31:46.252 --> 31:47.557
Everything's on fire!

31:47.601 --> 31:49.081
My turkey!Pru.

31:49.124 --> 31:50.517
I-It's okay.
Vic took her to Bailey.

31:50.560 --> 31:51.953
Open the patio door!

31:51.997 --> 31:53.824
Okay.
[ Grunting ]

31:56.044 --> 31:57.219
What are you doing?!

31:57.263 --> 31:58.917
I'm getting
that turkey out!

31:58.960 --> 32:00.353
[ Motor whirring ]Travis, that oven
is really expensive!

32:00.396 --> 32:01.702
Mom, please!

32:01.745 --> 32:03.965
[ Blaring continues ]

32:04.009 --> 32:10.058
♪♪

32:10.102 --> 32:12.191
Uh, Ingrid?

32:15.063 --> 32:19.850
You don't really
want to jump, do you?

32:19.894 --> 32:21.243
I-I don't think you do.

32:21.287 --> 32:22.766
You don't know me.

32:22.810 --> 32:24.768
I'm just some crazy lady

32:24.812 --> 32:27.467
who thought we were getting
romantically involved.

32:27.510 --> 32:28.555
Well, hey, you know what?

32:28.598 --> 32:30.209
I might be married,

32:30.252 --> 32:32.951
but the next guy
might not be.

32:32.994 --> 32:35.910
You are a person
who cares.

32:35.954 --> 32:40.001
You're grateful
and you're kind

32:40.045 --> 32:43.657
and anyone would be lucky
to have you around.

32:43.700 --> 32:45.354
But no one will be Scott.

32:47.182 --> 32:49.184
No.

32:49.228 --> 32:51.317
No one will.

32:51.360 --> 32:52.840
Life is painful.

32:52.883 --> 32:53.884
There's no two ways
about it.

32:53.928 --> 32:57.540
It's love
and it's grief...

32:57.584 --> 33:00.195
a-and it's love
and it's grief

33:00.239 --> 33:03.764
and it's love...
and it's grief,

33:03.807 --> 33:07.028
a-and our job --
our job

33:07.072 --> 33:12.164
is to make sure that
the love we feel...

33:12.207 --> 33:15.167
is worth the grief.

33:15.210 --> 33:21.608
♪♪

33:21.651 --> 33:24.437
Okay. There you go.

33:24.480 --> 33:26.091
Yeah.
I'm sorry.

33:26.134 --> 33:27.527
No, don't be sorry.

33:27.570 --> 33:28.876
Okay, you're okay.

33:28.919 --> 33:31.922
♪♪

33:31.966 --> 33:35.752
[ Alarm blaring ]

33:35.796 --> 33:37.406
Honey,
you don't have to --

33:37.450 --> 33:39.800
I paid 150 bucks
for this turkey!

33:39.843 --> 33:42.933
It's heritage!
It's organic!

33:42.977 --> 33:45.501
[ Coughs ] It's burning!
It's coming out if I have to --

33:45.545 --> 33:47.199
Okay, yeah, I heard it.

33:47.242 --> 33:48.591
Come on!

33:48.635 --> 33:49.897
[ Oven creaking ]Please!

33:49.940 --> 33:51.725
Ahh!

33:51.768 --> 33:53.988
[ Blaring continues ]

33:54.032 --> 33:59.689
♪♪

34:06.000 --> 34:07.349
[ Blaring stops ]

34:10.483 --> 34:11.745
[ Door opens ]

34:11.788 --> 34:14.356
What the...hell
happened here?

34:14.400 --> 34:18.012
I just destroyed an oven
that costs more than my car.

34:18.056 --> 34:20.145
What in holy hell
did you guys do?

34:21.711 --> 34:23.844
[ Groans ]

34:23.887 --> 34:25.019
You alright?

34:25.063 --> 34:27.978
Uh, yeah,
I'm -- I'm -- I'm good.

34:28.022 --> 34:30.720
[ Laughter ]

34:32.113 --> 34:33.854
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

34:33.897 --> 34:35.943
[ Laughter continues ]

34:35.986 --> 34:38.380
Yeah.
Yeah,
this seems about right.

34:38.424 --> 34:40.121
Well, I guess you don't
need this, then.

34:40.165 --> 34:41.340
All: No! No! No!

34:41.383 --> 34:42.471
Hey, hey!

34:42.515 --> 34:44.430
[ Laughs ]

34:44.473 --> 34:46.301
Andy: Whew.

34:46.345 --> 34:51.654
♪♪

34:51.698 --> 34:53.917
[ Crying quietly ]

34:53.961 --> 35:00.533
♪♪

35:00.576 --> 35:06.495
♪♪

35:06.539 --> 35:08.106
[ Crying continues ]

35:08.149 --> 35:14.155
♪♪

35:14.199 --> 35:16.636
I don't know why this happened.
I-I'm sorry.

35:16.679 --> 35:18.768
I -- [sniffles]
I swear I'm not crazy.

35:18.812 --> 35:20.161
I know. I know.

35:20.205 --> 35:22.207
I mean, grief is
a powerful thing,

35:22.250 --> 35:23.730
especially
on a day like today.

35:25.688 --> 35:26.863
So, listen,
my friend here

35:26.907 --> 35:28.952
is gonna take you
to Grey Sloan.

35:28.996 --> 35:30.432
The hospital?And they'll
check you out

35:30.476 --> 35:32.434
and get you the help
you need.

35:32.478 --> 35:34.349
I don't think I need --Ingrid.

35:34.393 --> 35:36.786
Your husband passed
from CO2 poisoning.

35:36.830 --> 35:38.527
You almost died
in a fire.

35:38.571 --> 35:40.181
You call the station
every day.

35:40.225 --> 35:42.183
You smell gas or smoke
every day.

35:42.227 --> 35:44.316
It's not gas.
It's not smoke.

35:44.359 --> 35:47.232
It's grief and PTSD,

35:47.275 --> 35:50.322
and you need to let the
professionals take over now

35:50.365 --> 35:52.585
and help...

35:52.628 --> 35:54.064
okay?

35:56.197 --> 35:57.459
Okay.

35:59.592 --> 36:01.071
And, hey, you know,

36:01.115 --> 36:02.551
come back and visit us,
you know,

36:02.595 --> 36:04.162
when you're
feeling better.

36:05.250 --> 36:06.686
Thank you.

36:06.729 --> 36:12.257
♪♪

36:12.300 --> 36:17.653
♪♪

36:17.697 --> 36:19.612
Dr. Bailey.

36:19.655 --> 36:20.526
Baby.

36:20.569 --> 36:21.918
Hey, baby.

36:21.962 --> 36:24.225
It's Grandpa.

36:24.269 --> 36:25.313
Hi.

36:27.010 --> 36:28.490
So cute.

36:28.534 --> 36:29.622
♪♪

36:29.665 --> 36:32.190
Oh, I missed you.

36:35.628 --> 36:37.760
Bill:
I understand that you love
my granddaughter very much,

36:37.804 --> 36:39.240
but it is Thanksgiving,

36:39.284 --> 36:40.807
and my wife has gone through
enough with Dean.

36:42.243 --> 36:43.810
She needs
her granddaughter.

36:43.853 --> 36:49.468
Mr. Miller, I cannot imagine
the loss you've suffered.

36:49.511 --> 36:51.948
I'm so deeply sorry.

36:51.992 --> 36:54.516
I'm so sorry
for your loss.

36:54.560 --> 36:57.302
[ Voice breaking ]
Your son was a wonderful man.

36:57.345 --> 37:00.305
Please,
please stay for dinner.

37:01.306 --> 37:03.612
Stay so you can
get to know us,

37:03.656 --> 37:06.615
'cause we don't
just love Pru,

37:06.659 --> 37:10.053
we -- we all are
her family, too.

37:10.097 --> 37:11.751
She's lost so much.

37:11.794 --> 37:15.624
She can't lose
this family --

37:15.668 --> 37:21.195
the family whose arms
she was literally born into.

37:21.239 --> 37:24.851
Yes, there's -- there's family
that blood makes,

37:24.894 --> 37:29.116
but there's also the family
made of this --

37:29.159 --> 37:32.772
made of shared experience

37:32.815 --> 37:35.601
and familiarity
and sensibility

37:35.644 --> 37:41.650
and shared passions
and understanding and love.

37:41.694 --> 37:43.304
Please.

37:43.348 --> 37:46.351
♪♪

37:46.394 --> 37:48.483
Alright.
We'll stay for dinner.

37:48.527 --> 37:50.572
Thank you.

37:50.616 --> 37:53.445
But after...

37:53.488 --> 37:55.273
I'm leaving
with my granddaughter.

37:55.316 --> 37:57.362
♪♪

37:57.405 --> 38:04.151
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

38:04.194 --> 38:08.286
♪ Well, my eyes are on
the high road ♪

38:08.329 --> 38:13.682
♪ And my back's
facing the sun ♪

38:13.726 --> 38:17.382
♪ The dark is coming
and the daylight's almost gone ♪

38:17.425 --> 38:21.429
♪ But a change is gonna come

38:21.473 --> 38:23.866
♪♪

38:23.910 --> 38:28.567
♪ Something on the horizon

38:28.610 --> 38:33.311
♪ Yeah, it's beating
like a drum ♪

38:33.354 --> 38:37.402
♪ I hear it coming
and I know it won't be long ♪

38:37.445 --> 38:42.711
♪ But a change is gonna come

38:42.755 --> 38:46.802
♪ A change is gonna come

38:46.846 --> 38:50.937
♪ A change is gonna come

38:50.980 --> 38:52.591
♪ Oh

38:52.634 --> 38:56.421
♪ It's getting hard to find
the strength to carry on ♪

38:56.464 --> 39:02.688
♪ But a change is gonna come

39:02.731 --> 39:06.996
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

39:07.040 --> 39:11.871
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

39:11.914 --> 39:16.397
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

39:16.441 --> 39:19.400
[ Indistinct conversations,
dishes clattering ]

39:19.444 --> 39:22.360
Look at him with her.
[ Sighs ]

39:24.797 --> 39:26.799
Today was a lot
for him.Mm.

39:28.453 --> 39:30.803
It was a lot
for everyone.

39:30.846 --> 39:33.545
Yeah, it was a disaster.
[ Laughs ]

39:33.588 --> 39:34.720
A pretty beautiful one.

39:36.983 --> 39:37.940
It was.

39:37.984 --> 39:39.159
Mm.

39:39.202 --> 39:40.508
I mean, all of it.

39:40.552 --> 39:43.772
There were disasters happening
in the kitchen...

39:43.816 --> 39:48.603
Mm-hmm....and in families
and on the roof...

39:48.647 --> 39:50.649
and we're all in pain
and heartbroken.

39:50.692 --> 39:51.737
Yeah.

39:51.780 --> 39:53.129
And yet...

39:53.173 --> 39:54.827
when there was
a child in the building,

39:54.870 --> 39:56.481
we were all fine.

39:56.524 --> 39:59.135
When there was a child
in my arms

39:59.179 --> 40:00.702
in the middle of it all,
I was fine.

40:00.746 --> 40:03.444
We kept her fine.
We knew how to keep her fine.

40:03.488 --> 40:05.446
We can do this.

40:05.490 --> 40:06.534
I can do this.

40:06.578 --> 40:08.406
Let's have a baby.

40:09.885 --> 40:11.017
Sorry, what?

40:11.060 --> 40:12.410
I want to have a baby.

40:14.237 --> 40:17.458
Okay, it's usually not best
to make decisions

40:17.502 --> 40:18.459
while in mourning.

40:18.503 --> 40:20.418
I'm not. I mean --

40:20.461 --> 40:24.987
I am in mourning, but...

40:25.031 --> 40:26.728
I've been thinking
this whole time

40:26.772 --> 40:28.556
that I needed to
stick to some plan,

40:28.600 --> 40:30.950
but plans don't work.

40:30.993 --> 40:33.953
People die.
Families fall apart.

40:36.521 --> 40:37.696
Let's have a baby.

40:39.349 --> 40:40.699
Mm-hmm.

40:41.613 --> 40:43.310
Are you serious?
Yes.

40:43.353 --> 40:45.181
[ Laughter ]

40:45.225 --> 40:46.705
There you go.
Choose.

40:46.748 --> 40:48.358
Thank you.Good pick.

40:55.453 --> 40:56.671
It's not how
it should have gone.

40:56.715 --> 40:58.543
Oh, Travis...
Okay.

40:58.586 --> 40:59.935
...please let's not
do this again.

40:59.979 --> 41:02.024
And who knows what mess
lies ahead,

41:02.068 --> 41:05.114
but just let me say...

41:05.158 --> 41:07.465
it gets better.

41:07.508 --> 41:10.293
I know from experience.

41:10.337 --> 41:13.819
This is the worst
it'll ever feel.

41:18.911 --> 41:20.303
You don't want to
join us for dinner?

41:20.347 --> 41:23.089
No, that sounds like
a 19 kind of thing.

41:23.132 --> 41:25.657
Well, you are
the captain of 19.

41:25.700 --> 41:27.702
I'm pretty sure
no one wants me there.

41:30.618 --> 41:32.838
No one blames you
for Miller's death.

41:32.881 --> 41:34.492
Everyone's just
glad you made it.

41:34.535 --> 41:37.930
You know,
if I had died,

41:37.973 --> 41:39.975
there'd be nobody to
take that phone call.

41:40.019 --> 41:42.761
My ex-wife's in Florida.
Parents are dead.

41:42.804 --> 41:46.678
My brother is an alcoholic
who doesn't take my calls.

41:46.721 --> 41:48.288
The only people
who might have mourned me

41:48.331 --> 41:49.550
are the people
in this building,

41:49.594 --> 41:51.160
and they'd be busy...

41:51.204 --> 41:53.423
mourning the guy
they actually liked.

41:53.467 --> 41:55.295
[ Sighs ]
[ Chuckles ]

41:56.862 --> 42:01.257
But, hey, if you ever, uh,
change your mind about

42:01.301 --> 42:02.955
taking me up
on that drink...

42:02.998 --> 42:05.174
A-Appreciate it, Beckett.

42:05.218 --> 42:06.915
Please call me Sean.

42:06.959 --> 42:08.482
Sean.
Mm-hmm.

42:08.526 --> 42:10.745
[ Chuckles ]

42:10.789 --> 42:12.617
Things are still messy
with Robert.

42:12.660 --> 42:14.444
It's just --

42:14.488 --> 42:15.533
It's just
not a good idea.

42:19.145 --> 42:21.147
Thank you for the pie.

42:23.323 --> 42:25.543
Yeah.
[ Chuckles lightly ]

42:36.379 --> 42:38.425
Bailey:
She's gonna wear him out.Bill: Arike!

42:38.468 --> 42:39.687
It's time to go.

42:39.731 --> 42:42.429
Oh -- Oh, you're using
her middle name?

42:42.472 --> 42:43.561
It is her true name.

42:43.604 --> 42:45.998
Th--This doesn't have to
be a battle.

42:46.041 --> 42:48.043
Alright, we all love her.

42:48.087 --> 42:50.568
You don't love her
as much as her grandparents do.

42:50.611 --> 42:51.873
Arike.

42:52.526 --> 42:53.658
[ Clears throat ]
Okay, w-when --

42:53.701 --> 42:55.050
when should we
pick her up?

42:56.051 --> 42:57.792
[ Sighs ]

42:58.837 --> 43:00.926
Thank you for dinner,

43:00.969 --> 43:03.102
and for looking after
my granddaughter.

43:03.145 --> 43:05.452
Oh. Here, baby.

43:05.495 --> 43:07.236
[ Chuckles ]

43:07.280 --> 43:09.325
Take care.

